vaeoicbokepmdiqgggyafmamjobcbadqrcycuetc length 5 70148 page 2759 American voice actor (1954–2023) Peter Spellos Born Peter Alexander Spellos (1954-03-01)March 1, 1954 Died November 19, 2023(2023-11-19) (aged 69) Indianapolis, Indiana, United States Occupation Voice actor Years active 1990–2023 Peter Alexander Spellos[1] (March 1, 1954 – November 19, 2023) was an American voice actor. Spellos appeared in hundreds of films and television shows. He died from pancreatic cancer on November 19, 2023, at the age of 69.[2] Notable roles[edit] Animated Television Series[edit] BattleTech: The Animated Series – Captain Miles Hawkins Bureau of Alien Detectors – Moose Trengganu Anime[edit] Black Jack – Mr. Brane Bleach – Koganehiko, Dordonii Alessandro del Socaccio Code Geass – Bartley Asprius Cowboy Bebop – Dr. Baucus (Episode 15) Digimon: Digital Monsters – Meramon, Whamon, Additional Voices Eagle Riders – Cyberon El-Hazard – Londs Ghost in the Shell: Stand Alone Complex – Niimi Gurren Lagann – Beastman (episode 13) Kikaider – Zadam Naruto – Hitode Outlaw Star – Gilliam Planetes – Hakim Ashmead[3] Rave Master – Billy S-CRY-ed – Dred The Big O – Additional Voices Transformers: Robots in Disguise – Sky-Byte Trigun – Monev The Gale Wolf's Rain – Bartender Live action[edit] American Dreams – Gus The Guyver – Ramsey ER – Trib Reporter Married... with Children – Elmo NewsRadio – Camera Man Lois and Clark: The New Adventures of Superman – Elroy Sykes Movie roles[edit] Billy Frankenstein – Bloodstone Bound – Lou Cowboy Bebop: The Movie – Duvchenko, Queen Digimon: Island of the Lost Digimon – Grizzlymon Dinosaur Island – Turbo Panda! Go, Panda! – Ringmaster Glass Trap – Howard Brunel Hard to Die – Orville Ketchum Men in Black II – Captain Larry Bridgewater Possessed by the Night – Big Ed Agent Red – Col. Korsky Sorority House Massacre II – Orville Ketchum In the Army Now – Mr. Quinn Yes Man – Security Guard (Hollywood Bowl) Video games[edit] Seven Samurai 20XX – Rojie[4] Star Ocean: S